<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,546,607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
The recognition of 
<taxonomicName box="[367,468,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acylophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="janaki">
<emphasis box="[367,468,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">A. janaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species among a series of specimens referred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lott" box="[1165,1293,546,570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" refString="Lott, D. A. (2010) The species of Acylophorus Nordmann (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae) in continental sub-Saharan Africa. Zootaxa, 2402, 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="2010">
Lott (
<number box="[1226,1285,546,570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[1329,1436,547,571]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acylophorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allardi">
<emphasis box="[1329,1436,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">A. allardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes it necessary to revise the diagnostic characters previously given for this species.
</paragraph>
